#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:0.5"
msgid "10. Rājasikkhāpada"
msgstr "10. The training rule on kings"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.220, pts-cs-bu-np10.1.1, pts-vp-en2.62, ms1V_2070
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhāko mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa dūtena cīvaracetāpannaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "At that time a government official who was a supporter of Venerable Upananda sent a robe fund to Upananda by messenger, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.3"
msgid "“iminā cīvaracetāpannena cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādehī”ti."
msgstr "“Buy a robe with this fund and give it to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho so dūto yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The messenger went to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.6"
msgid "“idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable, I’ve brought a robe fund for you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.7"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan”ti."
msgstr "Please accept it.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ dūtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.9
msgid "“na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, cīvarañca kho mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma kālena kappiyan”ti."
msgstr "“We don’t receive robe funds, but we do receive allowable robes at the right time.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.10"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, so dūto āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.11
msgid "“atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro”ti?"
msgstr "“Is there anyone who provides services for you?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.12"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako ārāmaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr "Just then a lay follower had come to the monastery on some business."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ dūtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Upananda told the messenger,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.14"
msgid "“eso kho, āvuso, upāsako bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro”ti."
msgstr "“This lay follower provides services for the monks.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.63
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.15"
msgid "Atha kho so dūto taṃ upāsakaṃ saññāpetvā yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The messenger instructed that lay follower and then returned to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.16"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.17"
msgid "“yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā."
msgstr "“I’ve instructed the lay follower you pointed out to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.18"
msgid "Upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī”ti."
msgstr "Please approach him at the right time and he’ll give you a robe.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2071
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.19"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena so mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "Later on that government official sent a message to Upananda, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.20"
msgid "“paribhuñjatu ayyo taṃ cīvaraṃ,"
msgstr "“Please use the robe;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.21"
msgid "icchāma mayaṃ ayyena taṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuttan”ti."
msgstr "we wish you to use the robe.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.22"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ upāsakaṃ na kiñci avacāsi."
msgstr "But Upananda did not say anything to that lay follower."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.23"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "The government official sent the same message a second time,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.24"
msgid "“paribhuñjatu ayyo taṃ cīvaraṃ, icchāma mayaṃ ayyena taṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuttan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.25"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ upāsakaṃ na kiñci avacāsi."
msgstr "but again Upananda did nothing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.26"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho so mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "The government official then sent the message a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.1.27"
msgid "“paribhuñjatu ayyo taṃ cīvaraṃ, icchāma mayaṃ ayyena taṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuttan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-cs-bu-np10.1.2, ms1V_2072
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena negamassa samayo hoti."
msgstr "On that occasion the householder association was having a meeting."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.2"
msgid "Negamena ca katikā katā hoti—"
msgstr "They had made an agreement"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.3"
msgid "“yo pacchā āgacchati paññāsaṃ baddho”ti."
msgstr "that whoever came late would be fined fifty coins."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.64
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena so upāsako tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Just then Upananda went to that lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.6"
msgid "“attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā”ti."
msgstr "“I need a robe.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.7"
msgid "“Ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehi, ajja negamassa samayo."
msgstr "“Venerable, please wait one day, for today there is a meeting of the householder association,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.8"
msgid "Negamena ca katikā katā hoti—‘yo pacchā āgacchati paññāsaṃ baddho’”ti."
msgstr "They have made an agreement that whoever comes late gets fined fifty coins."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.9"
msgid "“Ajjeva me, āvuso, cīvaraṃ dehī”ti"
msgstr "“Give me the robe today,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.10"
msgid "ovaṭṭikāya parāmasi."
msgstr "and he grabbed him by the belt."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.11"
msgid "Atha kho so upāsako āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena nippīḷiyamāno āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā pacchā agamāsi."
msgstr "Being pressured by Upananda, the lay follower bought him a robe, and as a consequence he was late for the meeting."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.12"
msgid "Manussā taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "People asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.13"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, ayyo, pacchā āgato,"
msgstr "“Sir, why are you late?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.14"
msgid "paññāsaṃ jīnosī”ti."
msgstr "You’ve just lost fifty coins.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, pts-vp-pli3.221, ms1V_2073
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.15"
msgid "Atha kho so upāsako tesaṃ manussānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "That lay follower told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.16"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And they grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.17"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.18"
msgid "Nayimesaṃ sukaraṃ veyyāvaccampi kātuṃ."
msgstr "Even to provide them with a service isn’t easy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.19"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando upāsakena—"
msgstr "How can Venerable Upananda not agree when he’s asked by a lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.20"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamessatī”ti."
msgstr "to wait for a day?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2074
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.21"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.22"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.23"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.24"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto upāsakena—"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda not agree when asked by a lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.25"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamessatī”ti."
msgstr "to wait for a day?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2075
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.26"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.65
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.27"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, upāsakena—"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.28"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamesī”ti?"
msgstr "that you acted like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.29"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.30"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.31"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, upāsakena—"
msgstr "“… Foolish man, how can you not agree when asked by a lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.32"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamessasi."
msgstr "to wait for a day?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.33"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.2.34"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-vp-pli3.222, pts-cs-bu-np10.1.3, ms1V_2076
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.1"
msgid "“Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissa rājā vā rājabhoggo vā brāhmaṇo vā gahapatiko vā dūtena cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇeyya—"
msgstr "‘If a king, a king’s employee, a brahmin, or a householder sends a robe fund for a monk by messenger, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.2"
msgid "‘iminā cīvaracetāpannena cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ cīvarena acchādehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Buy a robe with this robe fund and give it to monk so-and-so,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.3"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "and the messenger goes to that monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.4"
msgid "‘idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerable, I have brought a robe fund for you;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.5"
msgid "paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan’ti,"
msgstr "please accept it,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.6"
msgid "tena bhikkhunā so dūto evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "then that monk should reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.7"
msgid "‘na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "‘We don’t receive robe funds,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.8"
msgid "Cīvarañca kho mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, kālena kappiyan’ti."
msgstr "but we do receive allowable robes at the right time.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.9"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If that messenger says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.10"
msgid "‘atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro’ti,"
msgstr "‘Is there anyone who provides services for you?’,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.11"
msgid "cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro niddisitabbo ārāmiko vā upāsako vā—"
msgstr "the monk, if he needs a robe, should point out a monastery worker or a lay follower and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.12"
msgid "‘eso kho, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro’ti."
msgstr "‘He provides services for the monks.’"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.66
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.13"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ veyyāvaccakaraṃ saññāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If the messenger instructs that service-provider and then returns to the monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.14"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā,"
msgstr "‘Venerable, I have instructed the service-provider you pointed out;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.15"
msgid "upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī’ti,"
msgstr "please approach him at the right time and he will give you a robe,’"

#. VAR: dvattikkhattuṃ → dvittikkhattuṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.16"
msgid "cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro upasaṅkamitvā dvattikkhattuṃ codetabbo sāretabbo—"
msgstr "then, if that monk needs a robe, he should approach that service-provider and prompt him and remind him two or three times, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.17"
msgid "‘attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā’ti."
msgstr "‘I need a robe.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.18"
msgid "Dvattikkhattuṃ codayamāno sārayamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he then gets a robe, that is good."

#. VAR: chakkhattuparamaṃ → chakkhattuṃ paramaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.19"
msgid "no ce abhinipphādeyya, catukkhattuṃ pañcakkhattuṃ chakkhattuparamaṃ tuṇhībhūtena uddissa ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he does not get it, he should stand in silence for it at most six times."

#. VAR: kusalaṃ; tato → kusalaṃ no ce abhi­nip­phā­deyya tato (syā2, syā3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.20"
msgid "Catukkhattuṃ pañcakkhattuṃ chakkhattuparamaṃ tuṇhībhūto uddissa tiṭṭhamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he then gets a robe, that is good."

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.21"
msgid "tato ce uttari vāyamamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he makes any further effort and then gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.22"
msgid "No ce abhinipphādeyya, yatassa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ, tattha sāmaṃ vā gantabbaṃ dūto vā pāhetabbo—"
msgstr "If he does not get a robe, he should go to the owner of that robe fund, or send a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.23"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho tumhe āyasmanto bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇittha, na taṃ tassa bhikkhuno kiñci atthaṃ anubhoti,"
msgstr "‘Sirs, that monk hasn’t received any benefit from the robe fund you sent for him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.24"
msgid "yuñjantāyasmanto sakaṃ,"
msgstr "Please take action over what’s yours;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.25"
msgid "mā vo sakaṃ vinassā’ti,"
msgstr "let it not be lost.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:1.3.26"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti."
msgstr "This is the proper procedure.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-np10.2.1, ms1V_2077
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.2"
msgid "bhikkhussatthāya, bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā, bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmo."
msgstr "for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object of consideration, one desires to give to him."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2078
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.3"
msgid "Rājā nāma"
msgstr "A king:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.4"
msgid "yo koci rajjaṃ kāreti."
msgstr "whoever rules."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-en2.67, ms1V_2079
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.5"
msgid "Rājabhoggo nāma"
msgstr "A king’s employee:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.6"
msgid "yo koci rañño bhattavetanāhāro."
msgstr "whoever gets food and wages from a king."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2080
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.7"
msgid "Brāhmaṇo nāma"
msgstr "A brahmin:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.8"
msgid "jātiyā brāhmaṇo."
msgstr "a brahmin by birth."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2081
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.9"
msgid "Gahapatiko nāma"
msgstr "A householder:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.10"
msgid "ṭhapetvā rājaṃ rājabhoggaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ avaseso gahapatiko nāma."
msgstr "anyone apart from a king, a king’s employee, and a brahmin."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2082
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.11"
msgid "Cīvaracetāpannaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe fund:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.12"
msgid "hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā muttā vā maṇi vā."
msgstr "money, gold, a pearl, or a gem."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2083
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.13"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "With this robe fund:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.14"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "with that which is at one’s disposal."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2084
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.15"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "Buy:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.16"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_2085
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.17"
msgid "Acchādehīti"
msgstr "Give:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.18"
msgid "dajjehi."
msgstr "donate."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_2086
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.19"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "And the messenger goes to that monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.20"
msgid "“idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable, I have brought a robe fund for you;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.21"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan”ti,"
msgstr "please accept it,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.22"
msgid "tena bhikkhunā so dūto evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "then that monk should reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.23"
msgid "“na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "“We don’t receive robe funds,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.24"
msgid "Cīvarañca kho mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, kālena kappiyan”ti."
msgstr "but we do receive allowable robes at the right time.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.25"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If that messenger says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.26"
msgid "“atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro”ti?"
msgstr "“Is there anyone who provides services for you?”,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.27"
msgid "Cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro niddisitabbo ārāmiko vā upāsako vā—"
msgstr "the monk, if he needs a robe, should point out a monastery worker or a lay follower and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.28"
msgid "“eso kho, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro”ti."
msgstr "“He provides services for the monks”:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.29"
msgid "Na vattabbo—"
msgstr "he should not say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.30"
msgid "“tassa dehīti vā, so vā nikkhipissati, so vā parivattessati, so vā cetāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“Give it to him/he’ll put it aside/he’ll do the exchange/he’ll buy it.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_2087
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.31"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ veyyāvaccakaraṃ saññāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If the messenger instructs that service-provider and then returns to the monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.32"
msgid "“yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā."
msgstr "“Venerable, I have instructed the service-provider you pointed out;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.33"
msgid "Upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī”ti."
msgstr "please approach him at the right time and he will give you a robe,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.34"
msgid "Cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro upasaṅkamitvā dvattikkhattuṃ codetabbo sāretabbo—"
msgstr "then, if that monk needs a robe, he should approach that service-provider and prompt him and remind him two or three times, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.35"
msgid "“attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā”ti."
msgstr "“I need a robe”:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.36"
msgid "Na vattabbo—"
msgstr "he should not say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.37"
msgid "“dehi me cīvaraṃ, āhara me cīvaraṃ, parivattehi me cīvaraṃ, cetāpehi me cīvaran”ti."
msgstr "“Give me a robe/get me a robe/get a robe in exchange for me/buy me a robe.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="gloss">
#. REF: sc19, pts-vp-pli3.223, ms1V_2088
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.38"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "He should say it a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.39"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.40"
msgid "Sace abhinipphādeti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he gets it, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.41"
msgid "no ce abhinipphādeti, tattha gantvā tuṇhībhūtena uddissa ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he does not get it, [he should go there and] he should stand in silence for it:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.42"
msgid "Na āsane nisīditabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should not sit down on a seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.43"
msgid "Na āmisaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should not accept a gift."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.68
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.44"
msgid "Na dhammo bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "He should not give a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.45"
msgid "“Kiṃ kāraṇā āgatosī”ti pucchiyamāno"
msgstr "If he is asked, “Why have you come?”,"

# NOTE: _Jānāhi_. This verb, which normally means “to understand” or “to find out,” is used quite broadly in the Pali canon.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.46"
msgid "“jānāhi, āvuso”ti vattabbo."
msgstr "he should say, “Think about it.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.47"
msgid "Sace āsane vā nisīdati, āmisaṃ vā paṭiggaṇhāti, dhammaṃ vā bhāsati, ṭhānaṃ bhañjati."
msgstr "If he sits down on a seat, or he accepts a gift, or he gives a teaching, he loses one allowance to stand."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="gloss">
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_2089
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.48"
msgid "Dutiyampi ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should stand a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.49"
msgid "Tatiyampi ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.50"
msgid "Catukkhattuṃ codetvā catukkhattuṃ ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts four times, he can stand four times."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.51"
msgid "Pañcakkhattuṃ codetvā dvikkhattuṃ ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts five times, he can stand twice."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.1.52"
msgid "Chakkhattuṃ codetvā na ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts six times, he cannot stand at all."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: pts-cs-bu-np10.2.2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.1"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vāyamamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "If he makes any further effort and the robe then appears, he commits an offense of wrong conduct for the effort."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.2"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.69
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.6"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena abhinipphāditaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe which I got after prompting more than three times and standing more than six times is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.7"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.8"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.9"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.10"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_2090
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.11"
msgid "No ce abhinipphādeyya, yatassa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ tattha sāmaṃ vā gantabbaṃ dūto vā pāhetabbo—"
msgstr "If he does not get a robe, he should go to the owner of that robe fund, or send a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.12"
msgid "“yaṃ kho tumhe, āyasmanto, bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇittha na taṃ tassa bhikkhuno kiñci atthaṃ anubhoti."
msgstr "‘Sirs, that monk hasn’t received any benefit from the robe fund you sent for him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.13"
msgid "Yuñjantāyasmanto sakaṃ,"
msgstr "Please take action over what’s yours;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.14"
msgid "mā vo sakaṃ vinassā”ti."
msgstr "let it not be lost.’"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_2091
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr "This is the proper procedure:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.2.16"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "this is the right method."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc23, pts-cs-bu-np10.2.3, ms1V_2092
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.1"
msgid "Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena atirekasaññī abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, and he perceives that he has done so, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.2"
msgid "Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena vematiko abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, but he is unsure if he has, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.3"
msgid "Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena ūnakasaññī abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, but he perceives that it is less, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24, ms1V_2093
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.4"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, but he perceives that it is more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.5"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, but he is unsure if he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.3.6"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena ūnakasaññī anāpatti."
msgstr "If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, and he perceives that it is less, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc25, pts-cs-bu-np10.2.4, ms1V_2094
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.2"
msgid "tikkhattuṃ codanāya, chakkhattuṃ ṭhānena,"
msgstr "if he prompts three times and stands six time;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.70
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.3"
msgid "ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya, ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena,"
msgstr "if he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.4"
msgid "acodiyamāno deti,"
msgstr "if it is given without prompting;"

# NOTE: I am unable to make sense of the phrasing in the non-offense clause (_sāmikā codetvā denti_), and I therefore translate according to the phrasing in the commentary, “After prompting by the owners, it is given;” _sāmikehi codetvā dinne_, see [](Kkh. 119.6).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.5"
msgid "sāmikā codetvā denti,"
msgstr "if the owners prompt and then it is given;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc26, ms1V_2095
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.8"
msgid "Rājasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on kings, is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.9"
msgid "Kathinavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr "The first chapter on the robe-making season is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc27, ms1V_2096
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.10"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. HTML: </p><p class="uddana">
#. REF: sc28, ms1V_2097
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.11"
msgid "Ubbhataṃ kathinaṃ tīṇi,"
msgstr "Three on the ended robe-making season,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.12"
msgid "dhovanañca paṭiggaho;"
msgstr "And washing, receiving;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.13"
msgid "Aññātakāni tīṇeva,"
msgstr "Three on those who are unrelated,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:2.4.14"
msgid "ubhinnaṃ dūtakena cāti."
msgstr "Of both, and with messenger."
